        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: split plugin ClawHub publishing paths",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- split plugin ClawHub publishing into a normal OIDC release path and a protected token bootstrap path\n- route root release candidates so trusted existing packages use the OIDC workflow, while first-publish or trusted-publisher repair candidates use the bootstrap workflow\n- keep the normal ClawHub release workflow free of `CLAWHUB_TOKEN`, and keep the token scoped to the bootstrap workflow\n- pin the official ClawHub reusable publish workflow to the merged support commit and align ClawHub OIDC source metadata with the GitHub-attested release tag\n- make bootstrap recovery idempotent when a package version was created before trusted-publisher setup completed\n\n## Verification\n\n- `actionlint .github/workflows/plugin-clawhub-release.yml .github/workflows/plugin-clawhub-new.yml .github/workflows/openclaw-release-publish.yml`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/plugin-clawhub-release.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/release-beta-verifier.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Review notes\n\n- `autoreview` reported clean: no accepted/actionable findings.\n- The bootstrap workflow still pins `clawhub@0.20.2`; it validates that the pinned CLI exposes `package trusted-publisher set` before creating a package row, so the workflow will stop safely until a CLI version with that command is published and the pin is updated.\n",
